description=The CurriculumKG Ontology is an OWL 2 DL ontology for representing curricula, learning paths, personas, topics, media resources, and events, enabling dense interlinking of educational, learning, and training materials and supporting personalized, explainable neurosymbolic learning applications.
introduction=CurrKG models curricula as collections of modules, each covering topics, levels, categories, and associated media, and connects them to persona-specific learning paths that sequence learning steps over those modules. It is designed using modular ontology modeling and ontology design patterns (e.g., AgentRole and Sequence) to support reuse, extensibility, and alignment with broader knowledge graph ecosystems such as the Prototype Open Knowledge Network.
